metadata.description: Official Kangxi radicals with pronunciation from CC-CEDICT
sources: Unicode Standard (character codes and stroke counts)

meaning.cedict_definition: "dot" radical in Chinese characters (Kangxi radical 3), aka 點|点[dian3]
radical in Chinese characters (Kangxi radical 4), aka 撇[pie3]
second of the ten Heavenly Stems 十天干[shi2 tian1 gan1]
"vertical stroke with hook" radical in Chinese characters (Kangxi radical 6), aka 豎鉤|竖钩[shu4gou1]
radical in Chinese characters (Kangxi radical 13), occurring in 用[yong4], 同[tong2], 網|网[wang3] etc, referred to as 同字框[tong2 zi4 kuang4]
"cover" radical in Chinese characters (Kangxi radical 14), occurring in 軍|军[jun1], 冠[guan1] etc, known as 禿寶蓋|秃宝盖[tu1 bao3 gai4] or 平寶蓋|平宝盖[ping2 bao3 gai4]
"ice" radical in Chinese characters (Kangxi radical 15), occurring in 冰[bing1], 次[ci4] etc, known as 兩點水|两点水[liang3 dian3 shui3]
"right open box" radical (Kangxi radical 22), occurring in 区, 医, 匹 etc
"cover" or "conceal" radical in Chinese characters (Kangxi radical 23) (distinguished from 匚[fang1])
"cliff" radical in Chinese characters (Kangxi radical 27), occurring in 原, 历, 压 etc
"roof" radical (Kangxi radical 40), occurring in 家, 定, 安 etc, referred to as 寶蓋|宝盖[bao3 gai4]
(literary) person representing the deceased (during burial ceremonies)
"house on a cliff" radical in Chinese characters (Kangxi radical 53), occurring in 店, 序, 底 etc
"long stride" radical in Chinese characters (Kangxi radical 54), occurring in 建, 延, 廷 etc
step with the left foot (Kangxi radical 60)
abbr. for the Big Dipper constellation 北斗星[Bei3 dou3 xing1]
abbr. for 日本[Ri4 ben3], Japan
(bound form) family name; surname (as in 王氏[Wang2 shi4] "the Wang clan")
foot of a bird or animal
the solid and broken lines of the eight trigrams 八卦[ba1 gua4], e.g. ☶
"piece of wood" radical in Chinese characters (Kangxi radical 90), mirror image of 片[pian4]
to use; to make use of; to employ
Kangxi radical 105, known as 登字頭|登字头[deng1 zi4 tou2]
prefix used before the surname of a person or a numeral indicating the order of birth of the children in a family or to indicate affection or familiarity
used in 喇舌[la3 ji1] to transcribe the Taiwanese word for "tongue"

to walk (side part of split character)

abbr. for 青海[Qing1 hai3], Qinghai Province
abbr. for 非洲[Fei1 zhou1], Africa

abbr. for Heilongjiang province 黑龍江|黑龙江[Hei1 long2 jiang1]
ancient cooking cauldron with two looped handles and three or four legs
(name of states and dynasties at several different periods)
